sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;One of the most common sins, and </div><div class="t m7b0 x0 h4 y1c4a ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">one that is attended with most pernicious </div><div class="t ma34 x0 h4 y18b7 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">results, is the indulgence of an unforgiving </div><div class="t mae1 x0 h4 y17d1 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">spirit. How many will cherish animosity </div><div class="t m28f x0 h4 y28a ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">or revenge, and then bow before God and </div><div class="t m1734 x0 h4 y16b5 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ask to be forgiven as they forgive.&quot;-</div><div class="t mcdd xb7 h30 y19f5 ff6 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Testimonies, </div><div class="t m31c x66 h4 y19f5 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Vol. 5, p. 170. </div><div class="t m1209 x17 h33 yc5e ff1 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Christ&apos;s Spirit of Forgiveness </div><div class="t m988 x27 h4 y18a9 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m1c0a x18 h4 yebc ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How did Jesus set forth the law </div><div class="t m221f x0 h4 y1861 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of unlimited forgiveness in one of </div><div class="t mf60 x0 h4 y1593 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">His parables? Matt. 18:23-35. </div><div class="t m126f x92 h4 y188c ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTE.</div><div class="t m30cf x73 h5f y188c ff4 fs13 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">-&quot;The </div><div class="t ma0 x50 h4 y188c ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">great lesson of the parable </div><div class="t mbbe xb7 h4 y96f ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">lies in the contrast between God&apos;s com-</div><div class="t m995 xb7 h4 y17a4 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">passion and man&apos;s hardheartedness; in the </div><div class="t m449 xb7 h4 y19cb ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">fact that God&apos;s forgiving mercy is to be </div><div class="t m798 xb7 h4 y18f1 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the measure of our </div><div class="t m6f6 x10 h30 y111 ff6 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">own.&quot;-Christ&apos;s Object </div><div class="t m1648 xb7 h30 y18f2 ff6 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lessons, </div><di